com.vmware.vcenter.ovf

Interface ExportFlag

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExportFlagTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ExportFlagStub

    public interface ExportFlag
extends Service, ExportFlagTypes
    The ExportFlag interface provides methods for retrieving information about the export flags supported by the server. Export flags can be specified in a LibraryItemTypes.CreateSpec to customize an OVF export.

    • Method Detail

      • list

        java.util.List<ExportFlagTypes.Info> list()
        Returns information about the supported export flags by the server.

        The supported flags are:

        PRESERVE_MAC
        Include MAC addresses for network adapters.
        EXTRA_CONFIG
        Include extra configuration in OVF export.

        Future server versions might support additional flags.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Returns:
        A List of supported export flags.
        Throws:
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires System.Read.
